âœï¸ ğğ«ğšğœğ­ğ¢ğœğ ğ“ğ¢ğ©: The key is to remember the "ones + und + tens" rule for two-digit numbers within larger numbers. For years, Germans often say "nineteen hundred ninety" (neunzehnhundertneunzig) instead of "one thousand nine hundred ninety."

For example: ğŸ“Œ "Wann bist du geboren?" (When were you born?) "Ich bin (im Jahr) neunzehnhundertneunzig geboren." (I was born in (the year) 1990.)



